FBIS4-66032 "drweu103_p_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-103 Daily Report 26 May 1994 GREECE Protests Issued on Albanian Minority Arrests Protests Issued on Albanian Minority Arrests New Democracy Concerned NC2605164994 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1500 GMT 26 May 94 NC2605164994 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] New Democracy Chairman Miltiadhis Evert today held a news conference for the foreign and Greek press. During the news conference, he discussed our national issues, with particular emphasis on the increasing idealism of countries such as Albania. He also stressed the possible dangers that could result if the persecution against the Greek minority of Albania continues. Evert also referred to Turkey's aggressive role in the region. Finally, he accused the government of inaction on economic affairs.
